.TH "__post_watch_notification" 9 "__post_watch_notification" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__post_watch_notification \- Post an event notification
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __post_watch_notification
.BI "(struct watch_list *wlist "  ","
.BI "struct watch_notification *n "  ","
.BI "const struct cred *cred "  ","
.BI "u64 id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "wlist" 12
The watch list to post the event to.
.IP "n" 12
The notification record to post.
.IP "cred" 12
The creds of the process that triggered the notification.
.IP "id" 12
The ID to match on the watch.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Post a notification of an event into a set of watch queues and let the users
know.

The size of the notification should be set in n->info & WATCH_INFO_LENGTH and
should be in units of sizeof(*n).
